Sentencas: The understanding of the oxygen incorporation mechanism at the cathode is crucial for the improvement of solid oxide fuel cell performance.
Titulo: Surface Kinetics and Mechanism of Oxygen Incorporation Into Ba1-xSrxCoyFe1-yO3-δ SOFC Microelectrodes

Sentencas: To elucidate the reaction mechanism on the prototype cathode material Ba1-xSrxCoyFe1-yO3-delta (BSCF), the reaction kinetics is studied on geometrically well-defined dense thin film microelectrodes by impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Surface Kinetics and Mechanism of Oxygen Incorporation Into Ba1-xSrxCoyFe1-yO3-δ SOFC Microelectrodes

Sentencas: This avoids interference from the electrode morphology and allows a quantitative comparison of the oxygen incorporation rate for BSCF with different cation compositions.
Titulo: Surface Kinetics and Mechanism of Oxygen Incorporation Into Ba1-xSrxCoyFe1-yO3-δ SOFC Microelectrodes

Sentencas: The correlation between the effective surface exchange rate constant k extracted from the impedance spectra and various bulk properties is studied.
Titulo: Surface Kinetics and Mechanism of Oxygen Incorporation Into Ba1-xSrxCoyFe1-yO3-δ SOFC Microelectrodes

Sentencas: With oxygen diffusion coefficients reliably measured by oxygen isotope exchange and secondary ion mass spectrometry (SIMS), a correlation between k and the concentration and mobility of oxygen vacancies is confirmed.
Titulo: Surface Kinetics and Mechanism of Oxygen Incorporation Into Ba1-xSrxCoyFe1-yO3-δ SOFC Microelectrodes

Sentencas: Together with the temperature and oxygen partial pressure dependence of k, an oxygen incorporation mechanism on BSCF is proposed with a rate-determining step involving the migration of oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Surface Kinetics and Mechanism of Oxygen Incorporation Into Ba1-xSrxCoyFe1-yO3-δ SOFC Microelectrodes
